      "number": "1",
      "text": "Ensure that the parking brake is applied, and that the front and rear tires are secured with wheel stops. Start the engine. While pressing down firmly on the brake pedal, set the select lever to the D position and press down on the accelerator pedal, making sure that the engine does not stop when the pedal is abruptly released. Stop the vehicle in the middle of a hill. Turn the SELECT lever to the P position, release the brake and check the parking operation. Test driving on a flat road in D-position ECON ON, ECON OFF mode, and S-position, using HDS at the accelerator pedal position sensor voltage (accelerator pedal opening) specified in the driving position table to check vehicle speed and engine speed."
